# cap: constant adiabaticity pulse;
# constant amplitude wide-band adiabatic inversion pulse,
# adiabaticity is constant on resonance throughout the sweep in
# the rotating (phase modulated) frame, bandwidth increases with B1.
# J.Baum, R.Tycko, & A.Pines, Phys. Rev. 32 (1985) 3435. 
%
#       Shape Parameters
#       ----------------
fmf 	= cas	(frequency modulation function)
fla 	= 180.0	(default flipangle on resonance)
pwbw 	= 20.0	(pulsewidth to bandwidth product)
steps 	= 1500	(default number of steps)

